text:
Viruses that infect plants and animals can cause significant environmental damage, such as reducing yields, deteriorating food quality, and worsening animal welfare.
To prevent the release of viruses, preventive measures such as:
- Ensuring cleanliness and hygiene in production sites and production areas;
- Control of inputs and outputs from production sites;
- Use of antibiotics and other agents that provide an antiseptic effect;
- Regular monitoring of the situation at production sites and production areas;
- Use of genotypic methods to analyze the presence of viruses in plants and faces.
In case of detection of viruses, it is necessary to take immediate measures to eliminate them in order to prevent their spread and ensure environmental safety.
